H0.text: which material is the heaviest in term of density. Iridium

H2.text: which material is the heaviest in term of density. Rhenium

H3.text: which material is the heaviest in term of density. Osmium

A4.text: The measured density of iridium is only slightly lower (by about 0.12%) than that of osmium, the densest metal known.

A5.text: X-ray crystallographic data yielded densities of 22.56 g/cm3 (0.815 lb/cu in) for iridium and 22.59 g/cm3 (0.816 lb/cu in) for osmium.
